               <msContents>
                  <summary>

                    <locus target="#153v">Fol. 153v</locus>: colophon mentioning the scribe, Takla Maryam, and belonging to Head priest, Gabra Masqal.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="5r" to="157v" facs="005">Fols 5r–157v</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2701Dawit">Psalter</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1"><locus from="5r" to="125r" facs="005">Fols 5r–125r</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Mazmura Dāwit</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                  <note>The spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters are not given.  The sections are numbered, the letter is all that is written.</note>
                  <note><ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps151"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2000Mazmur#Ps151</span></ref> has all four plusses that make up the long version</note>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2"><locus from="125v" to="137r" facs="126">Fols 125v–137r</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1828Mahale">Book of Odes</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                  <note><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2257salota#Hannah">The Prayer of
                                                  Hannah, mother of Samuel the Prophet,
                                                  Hannah</title> is Prayer of Hana, mother of Samuel, prophet</note>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3"><locus from="137r" to="144r" facs="137">Fols 137r–144r</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2362Songof">Song of Songs</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                  <note>In the common version</note>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4"><locus from="144v" to="153r" facs="145">Fols 144v–153r</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2509Weddas">, arranged for the days of the week</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.1"><locus from="144v" facs="145">Fols 144v and following</locus><title>Monday</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.2"><locus from="145r" facs="145">Fols 145r and following</locus><title>Tuesday</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.3"><locus from="146v" facs="147">Fols 146v and following</locus><title>Wednesday</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.4"><locus from="148r" facs="148">Fols 148r and following</locus><title>Thursday</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.5"><locus from="150r" facs="150">Fols 150r and following</locus><title>Friday</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.6"><locus from="151r" facs="151">Fols 151r and following</locus><title>Saturday</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.7"><locus from="152r" facs="152">Fols 152r and following</locus><title>Sunday</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                </msItem>
              </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.5"><locus from="153r" to="157v" facs="153">Fols 153r–157v</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1113Anqasa">ʾAnqaṣa
                                                  bǝrhān</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                </msItem>
              </msItem>
               </msContents>
