                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word for God is not rubricated in the Psalms</desc>
                  <desc>There is columetric layout in the 10th biblical canticle, <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1566hababa#ThreeYouths3"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT1566hababa#ThreeYouths3</span></ref> and in <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps150"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2000Mazmur#Ps150</span></ref></desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="001">Fol. 1r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    several pen trials and scrawls
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#2r" facs="002">Fol. 2r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Instruction for recitation of an asmat prayer, incomplete, written in pencil
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#63v" facs="064">Fol. 63v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    The midpoint of the Psalms is unmarked
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc>
                    The spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters in <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps118">Psalms of
                                                  David, Psalmus 118</title> are not given. The sections are numbered, the letter is all that is written
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <desc>
                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps151">Psalms of
                                                  David, Psalmus 151</title>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <locus target="#129r" facs="129">Fol. 129r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    The fourth canticle is Prayer of Hana, mother of Samuel, prophet
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <locus target="#157v" facs="158">Fol. 157v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    notes
                    a) (bottom of column 1, written in black ink):
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘአፈ፡ ጸመኒ፡ በሰላመ። እግዚአብሔር። አሜን።</foreign>,
                    “For this book God helped me to finish in peace. Amen.”;
                    b) (bottom of column 1, written in red ink),
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሐፊሁ፡ ተክለ፡ ማርያም።</foreign>,
                    “Its scribe is Takla Maryam;”
                    c) (column 2, written in red ink),
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝንቱ፡ ዳዊት፡ ዘሊቀ፡ ካህናት፡ ገብረ፡ መስቀል፡ ዘአዋረዮ፡ በንዋዩ፡ ወብእሲቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ትንሣኤ። ዘተጽሕፈ። በ፲ወ፭፡ አነዳ፡ ጠሊ። ። ኦአምላከ፡ ዳዊት፡ አድኅነኒ፡ እመክራ፡ ሥጋ፡ ወነፍስ፡ ለገብርከ፡ ተክለ፡ ማርያም፡</foreign>,
                    “This Dawit belongs to Head Priest, Gabra Masqal, which he bought with his own money, and his wife, Walatta Tensie; it was written in 15 goat hides, O God of David, save me from the trials of body and soul for your servant, Takla Maryam
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
                <bindingDesc>
                  <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="partly">
                    <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment. Simple wooden boards, the front is broken and stitched.</decoNote>
                    <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                      <material key="parchment"/>
                      <material key="wood"/>
                    </decoNote>
                  </binding>
                </bindingDesc>
               </physDesc>
